header.gameNote: JOHN THOMPSON FOUNDATION CLASSIC AT COLUMBIA MO

article.headline: Army 80, Stetson 68
article.story: COLUMBIA, Mo. (AP) -- Matt Bell scored 20 points and keyed a 19-2 first-half run in Army's 80-68 season-opening victory over Stetson on Friday in the John Thompson Foundation Classic. Jarell Brown added 16 points and was 4-for-6 from 3-point range for Army, which was 5-22 last season. Bell, who made his 82nd straight start, added four steals. Missouri played North Carolina A&T later Friday in the first day of the three-day, round-robin tournament. Ten of Bell's points came in a 4-minute span that lifted Army from a 10-4 deficit to a 23-12 lead with 12 minutes to go in the first half. During the run he scored seven straight points, including two 3-pointers. Army shot 58 percent in the first half to take a 41-27 lead and extended that to 20 points on three occasions in the second half. The Black Knights shot 55 percent overall and were 9-for-12 from 3-point range. Gabe McMillen had 20 points for Stetson, going 7-for-11 from the field. Eric Diaz was 4-for-6 from 3-point range and had 16 points, and Garfield Blair also had 16 points. Stetson is coming off a 14-18 season. This was the second meeting between the schools, and first since 1984.
